    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-11T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-11T19:00:00-05:00" n="556"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.154/370: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-11T17:00:00-07:00"
                            >December 11, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>407. Referring to Department’s instruction No. 413, October 15th, note received
                    today from Foreign Office states permission granted as requested for possible
                    landings in Mexico of army airplanes to be used in aerial survey.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[Final details of the reconnaissance survey were not completed until 1933.
                        For full report of the survey prepared by the Bureau of Public <pb
                            facs="0829" n="715" xml:id="pg_715"/> Roads, Department of Agriculture,
                        see Senate Document 224, 73d Cong., 2d sess.: <hi rend="italic">Proposed
                            Inter-American Highway.</hi>]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
